Analytics

<span key="cc118b5be77d4d9c9de0dc85a1e1e707"><span offset-key="cc118b5be77d4d9c9de0dc85a1e1e707:0">I find analytics that is not actionable in any way a waste of time. For example, checking the Insights Traffic pane on GitHub on your own repos to see how many people viewed your repo or cloned it.</span></span>

<span key="4aee98eeec864d49b6736c7291c02aaa"><span offset-key="4aee98eeec864d49b6736c7291c02aaa:0">Well implemented analytics will let you see how to optimize your system to serve some end goals better and for that you need data. As well as know from where the traffic is coming from.</span></span>

<span key="3c6440ab701f470da67abb0321f262d7"><span offset-key="3c6440ab701f470da67abb0321f262d7:0">If analytics are used, it's best to implement them server side with something like </span></span><a href="https://www.netlify.com/products/analytics/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="711a7f1fc9094c96a2929f3746181369" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-9119_259-9120-237__"><span data-key="231760cc4b7a49059914248a93afa7be"><span data-offset-key="231760cc4b7a49059914248a93afa7be:0">Netlify</span></span></span></a><span key="d0c9c8cd74a3428a8d0a9c5306dc67f5"><span offset-key="d0c9c8cd74a3428a8d0a9c5306dc67f5:0"> so as to not send unnecessary JS to the client and keep pages light.</span></span>
